# T5d trigger bridge proof - 2026-05-22

Purpose: prove a bounded target-agent activation path using the local
`scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs` bridge.

This is not native Pentagon app poller proof. It is a workspace bridge that uses
Pentagon's existing public cloud surfaces:

- `agent_triggers` readback
- `claim_agent_trigger(p_trigger_id)`
- `mint-agent-token`
- Codex with the minted Pentagon MCP token
- `messages` visible response persistence
- `complete_agent_trigger(p_trigger_id)`

## Bridge script validation

```text
$ node --check scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs
exit 0

$ node scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs --dry-run --limit 3
status: ok
processed: 3
result statuses: would_process, would_process, would_process

$ node scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs --dry-run --limit 5 --max-age-seconds 60
status: idle
processed: 0
```

Safety controls:

```text
--max-age-seconds <n> filters pending triggers to recent rows only, so a loop
can avoid draining stale historical triggers.
--loop --interval-ms <n> keeps checking for fresh triggers at a fixed cadence.
```

